# Storage Area Network (SAN) - ‡§π‡§ø‡§Ç‡§¶‡•Ä + English

## üî∏ What is SAN? (SAN ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à?)

**English:**  
A Storage Area Network (SAN) is a high-speed network that connects storage devices (like hard drives) to servers. It allows multiple servers to access the same storage as if it were their own local disk.

**Hindi:**  
Storage Area Network (SAN) ‡§è‡§ï ‡§§‡•á‡§ú‡§º ‡§®‡•á‡§ü‡§µ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ï ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à ‡§ú‡•ã storage devices (‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•á hard drives) ‡§ï‡•ã servers ‡§∏‡•á ‡§ú‡•ã‡§°‡§º‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§á‡§∏‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡§à servers ‡§è‡§ï ‡§π‡•Ä storage ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ê‡§∏‡•á access ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§ï‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§µ‡•ã ‡§â‡§®‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ñ‡•Å‡§¶ ‡§ï‡•Ä local disk ‡§π‡•ã‡•§

---

## üîπ Why use SAN? (SAN ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§â‡§™‡§Ø‡•ã‡§ó ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç?)

**English:**
- Centralized storage management  
- Fast data access and transfer  
- Scalability (easy to add more storage)  
- High performance and availability  

**Hindi:**
- ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ú‡§ó‡§π ‡§∏‡•á ‡§™‡•Ç‡§∞‡•Ä storage ‡§ï‡•ã manage ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡§æ  
- ‡§§‡•á‡§ú‡§º‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•á data access ‡§î‡§∞ transfer ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡§æ  
- ‡§ú‡§º‡§∞‡•Ç‡§∞‡§§ ‡§™‡§°‡§º‡§®‡•á ‡§™‡§∞ storage ‡§¨‡§¢‡§º‡§æ‡§®‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§∏‡§æ‡§®  
- ‡§Ö‡§ö‡•ç‡§õ‡§æ performance ‡§î‡§∞ availability  

---

## üî∏ How SAN Works (SAN ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à?)

**English:**  
SAN uses a separate network (usually Fibre Channel or iSCSI) to connect storage devices and servers. It works like this:  
1. Servers send data requests through SAN.  
2. SAN delivers data from storage back to the server.  
3. Applications treat it like a local disk.  

**Hindi:**  
SAN ‡§è‡§ï ‡§Ö‡§≤‡§ó ‡§®‡•á‡§ü‡§µ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ï (‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•á Fibre Channel ‡§Ø‡§æ iSCSI) ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§â‡§™‡§Ø‡•ã‡§ó ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à:  
1. Server data ‡§ï‡§æ request ‡§≠‡•á‡§ú‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§  
2. SAN ‡§∏‡•á storage data ‡§µ‡§æ‡§™‡§∏ server ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¶‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§  
3. Application ‡§â‡§∏‡•á local disk ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§§‡§∞‡§π ‡§á‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡•á‡§Æ‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡•Ä ‡§π‡•à‡•§  

---

## üîπ SAN vs NAS (SAN ‡§î‡§∞ NAS ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§§‡§∞)

| Feature          | SAN                          | NAS                          |
|------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Network Type     | Block-level                   | File-level                    |
| Speed            | Faster                        | Slower                        |
| Use Case         | Databases, high-speed apps    | File sharing, backups         |
| Protocol         | Fibre Channel, iSCSI          | NFS, SMB                      |

---

## üî∏ Summary (‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞‡§æ‡§Ç‡§∂)

- SAN is used for fast, block-level storage access.  
- Best for large enterprise apps, databases, and virtualization.  
- Expensive but powerful.

**Hindi:**  
- SAN ‡§§‡•á‡§ú‡§º ‡§î‡§∞ block-level storage access ‡§¶‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§  
- ‡§¨‡§°‡§º‡•á systems ‡§î‡§∞ databases ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§Ö‡§ö‡•ç‡§õ‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§  
- ‡§Æ‡§π‡§Ç‡§ó‡§æ ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à, ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§¨‡§π‡•Å‡§§ ‡§§‡§æ‡§ï‡§º‡§§‡§µ‡§∞ ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§  
